I tried building vrx from source by following steps from [#!/osrf/vrx/wiki/tutorials/SystemSetupInstall](#!/osrf/vrx/wiki/tutorials/SystemSetupInstall).

By typing : roslaunch vrx\_gazebo sandisland.launch 

I am getting following warnings and gazebo is not loading. I am using ros melodic gazebon 9.0

‌

Warning \[[parser.cc:759](http://parser.cc:759)\] XML Attribute\[xmlns:xacro\] in element\[sdf\] not defined in SDF, ignoring.  
Warning \[[parser.cc:759](http://parser.cc:759)\] XML Attribute\[xmlns:xacro\] in element\[world\] not defined in SDF, ignoring.  
\[ INFO\] \[1567228563.020945111\]: Finished loading Gazebo ROS API Plugin.  
\[ INFO\] \[1567228563.023336032\]: waitForService: Service \[/gazebo\_gui/set\_physics\_properties\] has not been advertised, waiting...  
Warning \[[parser.cc:950](http://parser.cc:950)\] XML Element\[selfCollide\], child of element\[model\] not defined in SDF. Ignoring\[selfCollide\]. You may have an incorrect SDF file, or an sdformat version that doesn't support this element.  
Warning \[[parser.cc:950](http://parser.cc:950)\] XML Element\[static\], child of element\[link\] not defined in SDF. Ignoring\[static\]. You may have an incorrect SDF file, or an sdformat version that doesn't support this element.

Warning \[[parser.cc:950](http://parser.cc:950)\] XML Element\[static\], child of element\[link\] not defined in SDF. Ignoring\[static\]. You may have an incorrect SDF file, or an sdformat version that doesn't support this element.  
\[ INFO\] \[1567228568.034051437, 0.001000000\]: Thruster namespace <wamv/>  
\[ INFO\] \[1567228568.097589335, 0.023000000\]: waitForService: Service \[/gazebo/set\_physics\_properties\] is now available.

\[spawn\_model-4\] process has finished cleanly
